name: firewall

embeds.title: Common mistake
embeds.description: Error: `Could not connect to a default or fallback server. Incorrectly configured address/port/firewall?`

fields.name: Fix :flag_gb: English
fields.value:
Please use exactly the same Minecraft client version as your Minecraft server.
For example: 1.18.1 server with 1.18.1 clients.

If you are using the ViaVersion plugin, please use the latest version and only upload the plugin to your Spigot server.
Please also note that you may also need ViaRewind and ViaBackwards.

fields.name: Fix :flag_de: Deutsch
fields.value:
Bitte verwende genau dieselbe Minecraft-Client-Version wie die deines Minecraft-Servers.
Beispiel: 1.18.1-Server mit 1.18.1-Clients.

Wenn du das ViaVersion-Plugin verwendest, benutze bitte die neueste Version und laden das Plugin nur auf den Spigot-Server hoch.
Bitte beachte auch, dass m√∂glicherweise auch die Plugins ViaRewind und ViaBackwards ben√∂tigt werden.

embeds.title: What is the potency?
embeds.description:
:flag_gb: **English**
The potency is used to determine the importance of the permission.
In the case of positive numbers, the permission is granted with the corresponding strength; in the case of negative numbers, the permission is deducted with the corresponding strength.

:flag_de: **Deutsch:**
Die Potency dient dazu, die Wichtigkeit der Permission festzulegen. 
Bei positiven Zahlen wird die Permission mit der entsprechenden St√§rke vergeben, bei negativen Zahlen wird die Permission mit der entsprechenden St√§rke abgezogen.

embeds.title: CloudNet Placeholders
embeds.description:
**Signs:**
%task% ----------------------- The name of the task of the server on the sign
%task_id% -------------------- The id of the service (example: Lobby-1 -> 1)
%group% ---------------------- The targetGroup of the sign
%name% ----------------------- The name of the service on the sign
%uuid% ----------------------- The uuid of the service on the sign
%node% ----------------------- The name of the node the service on the sign is running on
%environment% ---------------- The environment of the service on the sign
%life_cycle% ----------------- The current life cycle of the service on the sign
%runtime% -------------------- The runtime of the service on the sign (Normally "jvm")
%port% ----------------------- The port of the service on the sign
%cpu_usage% ------------------ The current cpu usage of the service on the sign
%threads% -------------------- The current amount of threads of the service on the sign
%online% --------------------- "Online" or "Offline"
%online_players% ------------- The current amount of online players of the service on the sign
%max_players% ---------------- The current amount of max players of the service on the sign
%motd% ----------------------- The current motd of the service on the sign
%extra% ---------------------- The current extra of the service on the sign (can only be set with the API)
%state% ---------------------- The current state of the service on the sign (can only be set with the API)
%version% -------------------- The server version of the service on the sign
%whitelist% ------------------ "Enabled" or "Disabled" - Spigots whitelist
 
**Tablist Header/Footer:**
%proxy% ---------------------- The name of the proxy the player is connected to
%proxy_uniqueId% ------------- The uuid of the proxy the player is connected to
%server% --------------------- The name of the server the player is connected to
%online_players% ------------- The current amount of online players on the network
%max_players% ---------------- The current amount of max players on the network
%proxy_task_name% ------------ The name of the task of the proxy the player is connected to
%task% ----------------------- The name of the task of the server the player is connected to
%name% ----------------------- The name of the player
%ping% ----------------------- The current ping of the player
%time% ----------------------- The current time - Format: Hour:Minute:Second
%group% ---------------------- The name of the players highest permission group
%prefix% --------------------- The prefix of the players highest permission group
%suffix% --------------------- The suffix of the players highest permission group
%display% -------------------- The display of the players highest permission group
%color% ---------------------- The color of the players highest permission group
 
**Motd:**
%proxy% ---------------------- The name of the proxy the motd has been sent from
%proxy_uniqueId% ------------- The uniqueId of the proxy the motd has been sent from
%task% ----------------------- The name of the task of the proxy the motd has been sent from
%node% ----------------------- The node the proxy the motd has been sent from is running on
%online_players% ------------- The current amount of online players on the network
%max_players% ---------------- The current amount of max players on the network

**Stop the cloud for this**, change *database_provider* to `mysql` (or what is set in the config of the MySQL module) in `local/registry`.
Now just enter the data correctly in the MySQL module and start CloudNet again. Now everything should be saved in the MySQL database (**Previous data from H2 will not be automatically copied to the new MySQL database**)

fields.name: :flag_de: Deutsch
fields.value:
**Dazu die Cloud stoppen**, in `local/registry` *database_provider* auf `mysql` (bzw. das, was in der Config des MySQL Moduls eingestellt ist) umstellen.
Jetzt nur noch die Daten im MySQL Modul korrekt eintragen und CloudNet wieder starten. Nun sollte alles in der MySQL Datenbank gespeichert werden (**Bisherige Daten aus H2 werden nicht automatisch in die neue MySQL Datenbank kopiert**)

fields.name: :flag_gb: English
fields.value:
To activate snapshots, you must set the option `cloudnet.snapshots.use-snapshots` to `true` in the file `launcher.cnl` and then restart the cloud. In addition, you can also define a URL to select a specific snapshot variant. We will inform you of this when a snapshot is announced.
If snapshots are activated, the Cloud downloads the latest snapshot with every restart.

To stop using snapshots, stop the Cloud and set the `cloudnet.snapshots.use-snapshots` option in the `launcher.cnl` file back to `false`. Then delete the `launcher/versions` folder and restart the cloud.

fields.name: :flag_de: Deutsch
fields.value:
Um Snapshots zu aktivieren, m√ºsst ihr in der Datei `launcher.cnl` die Option `cloudnet.snapshots.use-snapshots` auf `true` setzen und danach die Cloud neustarten. Zus√§tzlich dazu l√§sst sich auch eine URL definieren, um eine bestimmte Snapshot-Variante auszuw√§hlen. Diese werden wir euch gegebenenfalls bei der Ank√ºndigung eines Snapshots mitteilen.
Wenn Snapshots aktiviert sind, l√§dt die Cloud bei jedem Neustart den neusten Snapshot herunter.

Um keine Snapshots mehr zu nutzen, m√ºsst ihr die Cloud stoppen und die Option `cloudnet.snapshots.use-snapshots` in der Datei `launcher.cnl` wieder auf `false` setzen. Danach m√ºsst ihr den Ordner `launcher/versions` l√∂schen und anschlie√üend die Cloud wieder starten.
